@ThaxanNumber14: And now I rated your comment a five.  
@TPmanW: It's rated as low as it is the same reason [Jace, the Mind Sculptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor) is rated around a 4.1. It's hated.  

Anyways, I rarely see it around anymore, mainly in Caw Blade sideboards. It's not the hated, presumably broken card it once was. However, that won't stop it from kicking your ass.

This thin is scary. I mean, it's really powerful. I think that what really does it is that there is nothing comparable at the same CMC. I mean, if there were a 5/5 angel for 5, this would be okay, but this has first strike. I mean, just one hit on a player is enough to swing the game a lot--10 point life difference is very significant. I feel that this is a little overpowered, if only because any hit swings the owner 5 life at least. Plus, nothing short of straight kill spells/[Dismember](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dismember) don't do anything to it. So yes, I don't think that power creep is as bad as many people say, but I do feel that mythics get an unnecessarily high power level  
/rant  

